quran[11]{c,v,t,f}:
  39,57,"or says, “If only Allah had guided me, I would have been among the righteous”;",""
  39,58,"or says, upon seeing the punishment, “If only I had another chance<sup>17</sup>, I could be among those who do good.”","[17] Of the worldly life."
  39,59,"[Allah will say,] “No indeed! My verses had already come to you, but you rejected them and acted arrogantly, and you were among the disbelievers.”",""
  39,60,"On the Day of Resurrection, you will see those who lied against Allah with their faces darkened. Is there not in Hell an abode for the arrogant?",""
  39,61,"But Allah will save those who fear Him, for they have attained salvation<sup>18</sup>; no harm will touch them, nor will they grieve.","[18] i.e., they succeeded in the trials of the life of this world and the attainment of Paradise."
  39,62,"Allah is the Creator of all things, and He is the Guardian over everything.",""
  39,63,"To Him belong the keys of the heavens and earth. As for those who disbelieve in the verses of Allah, it is they who are the losers.",""
  39,64,"Say [O Prophet], “Do you order me to worship other than Allah, O ignorant people?”",""
  39,65,"It has already been revealed to you and to those who came before you that if you associate others with Allah, your deeds will surely become worthless, and you will certainly be among the losers.",""
  39,66,"Rather, worship Allah alone and be among those who are grateful.",""
  39,67,"They did not revere Allah His true reverence<sup>19</sup>. On the Day of Resurrection, the whole earth will be in His Grip, and the heavens will be rolled up in His Right Hand. Glorified and exalted is He above all what they associate with Him!","[19] As they worshiped beside Him unable and weak creatures."
